    "recap_headline": "Rice University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "TAMPA, Fla. \u2014 Rice was held to just five hits, as South Florida grabbed the rubber game of the series, 7-2, Sunday afternoon.\nBoth pitchers held each other in check through the first two innings, but Rice took advantage in the third. After a leadoff walk to\nMason Ashlock\n,\nAric Anderson\nconnected on his first career triple.\nLandis Davila\nthen drove him in with a sacrifice fly.\nUSF answered in the bottom half of the inning. With one out, the Bulls got three straight singles. Eli Thomas followed with a double, tying the game at two. South Florida took the lead in the fifth. Bradke Lohry walked, and Thomas tripled. Nathan Early followed with his first home run of the year over the right field wall, forcing Rice to go to\nTy Thames\n. After a pair of singles, Jacob Green drove in Lance Trippel with a double.\nSouth Florida added a run in the sixth.\nKaden Smith moved to 3-1 with the win.\nEthan Sanders\n(1-3) went 4.0 innings to take the loss.\nUp Next\nRice will stay in Houston this Wednesday, Mar. 25, when it faces HCU at Husky Field. First pitch is scheduled for 6:30 p.m., and the game will be streamed by ESPN+.",
